Sentencas: Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-delta (PSCFNx, x = 0.1, 0.2) catalysts are prepared and utilized as electrodes in symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) for the hydrogen oxidation reaction (HOR) and oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Although the PSCFNx cathode retains its perovskite phase during operation in SOFCs, the anode is totally decomposed and decorated with an exsolved metallic Ni-Fe alloy (denoted as re-PSCFNx) in a reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) combined with distribution of relaxation times (DRT) analysis reveals that the rate-limiting step for the HOR at the anode is the hydrogen adsorption-dissociation process, while the charge transfer process is found to dominate the ORR at the cathode.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: As the doping of Ni is increased, the cathode polarization resistance for the ORR decreases from 0.19 Omega cm(2) for PSCFN0.1 to 0.09 Omega cm(2) for PSCFN0.2 at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A similar trend is observed for the anode polarization resistance for the HOR, which exhibits a reduction from 2.46 Omega cm(2) of re-PSCFN0.1 to 1.28 Omega cm(2) of re-PSCFN0.2 at 800 degrees C in H-2.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: When fueled with hydrogen, a single cell based on the PSCFN0.2/La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM)(240 mu m)/re-PSCFN0.2 configuration delivers a maximum power density of 623 mW cm(-2) and slight performance degradation when operated for 220 h at 800 degrees C. Ni doping results in the charge redistribution of B-site ions.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Increasing the doping level of Ni results in additional electron transfer channels and oxygen vacancies that adsorb more oxygen species, which facilitates the ORR performance.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Furthermore, an increase in the number of Ni-Fe nanoparticles and creation of abundant interfaces in the anode promote the HOR.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This work suggests that PSCFN0.2 has the potential to be an excellent electrode material for a symmetric SOFC.
Titulo: Bifunctional electrocatalysts Pr0.5Sr0.5Cr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2) for the HOR and ORR of a symmetric solid oxide fuel cell
